{[#]} 15. a5 $1 {Those of you who are familiar with the lecture should play
this move automatically. The idea is to create queenside weaknesses.} c4 16.
Qc2 b5 17. a6 $1 {When possible, we push the pawn all the way to a6!} Bc8 {
[%cal Gc8f5] The bishop is heading to f5.} 18. Bxe5 $1 {Another instructive
move. Since our opponent has a space advantage, we shouldn't let him keep his
knight. After} Bxe5 19. Nf3 Bf5 20. Qd2 Rfd8 21. Nxe5 Qxe5 22. Qd4 Qxd4 23.
Rxd4 $14 {[%csl Rd5][%cal Ge2f3,Ga1d1] White keeps a slight edge due to the
possibility to put pressure on d5. The next moves will be Bf3 followed by Rad1.
} 1/2-1/2

