{[#]} 1. a5 $1 {Sometimes, this thematic idea is possible even in positions
with a black knight on c6. Black cannot take on a5 due to the unprotected
b7-bishop.} c4 2. Qb5 Rc8 3. axb6 Qxb6 4. Qxb6 axb6 5. Nxe5 $1 {We know that
exchanging pieces is an important part of White's strategy. In this case, the
e5-pawn is getting even more vulnerable.} Bxe5 6. Bxe5 Nxe5 7. Rfd1 $16 {
[%csl Rb5,Rb6,Rd5][%cal Gd2b1,Gb1a3,Ga3c2,Gc2b4,Gb4d5,Ga3b5] White is clearly
better. He can increase the pressure by means of the manoeuvre Nd2-b1-a3-c2-b4.
In some cases, the knight can go to b5 as well.} *

