{The following example clearly shows White's potential on the open c-file.} 14.
Qb6 $1 {[%cal Gc3b3,Gf1c1,Gf3e1,Ge1d3,Gd3c5] White makes use of the weakened
dark squares on the queenside. He is planning to proceed with Rb3 followed by
Rfc1, and Nf3-e1-d3-c5.} f6 15. Rb3 Ra7 16. Rc1 Rc8 17. Ne1 {[%cal Ge1d3,Gd3c5]
} g5 18. Bh2 Bf5 19. Nd3 {[%cal Gd3c5]} Bxd3 {Black is forced to part with the
bishop pair. Otherwise, Nc5 is on the agenda.} 20. Bxd3 e6 21. Rbc3 Bf8 22. Bc2
$1 {The final touch. White is transferring his bishop to a4 and the game is
over.} a5 23. Ba4 $18 1-0

