14... Nxd5 {We can start from this critical position. We have a typical
endgame with the open "d" file. The question here is what to do with the
bishop.} 15. Bg3 $1 {This is the correct move. We need to keep the bishops on
the board.} Nb6 {Black is trying to stop Nc4} 16. Rad1 Rfd8 17. Rxd8+ Rxd8 18.
Bc7 Ra8 $1 {The only good move in this position.} (18... Rd2 $2 19. Bxb6 axb6
20. Nc4 Rc2 $2 21. a4 {stopping b5 and now the rook is just trapped} f5 22. Rb1
$18 {[%cal Rc4d2,Re1d1,Rg1f1,Rf1e1]}) (18... Rd7 19. Bxb6 axb6 20. Nb5 Rd2 21.
Rb1 $14 {[%cal Ra2a4,Rg1f1,Rf1e1] Black can't keep his rook on the second rank}
) 19. Rd1 (19. Bxb6 $2 {is premature} axb6 20. Ra1 $2 (20. Rc1 b5 $1 $15) 20...
Bxc3 $1 $19) 19... Na4 20. Rd2 Rc8 21. Bg3 c4 22. Kf1 a6 23. Bh4 Kf8 24. Rd7 $6
Nxb2 $2 25. Bxe7+ Kg8 26. Rxb7 Bxc3 27. Ke2 a5 28. Nb5 Be5 29. Bd6 Bf6 30. Rc7
$1 Rxc7 31. Bxc7 a4 32. Kd2 Nd3 33. f3 $2 Nb4 34. a3 Nd5 $2 35. Ba5 $2 Bb2 $2
36. e4 c3+ 37. Bxc3 Nxc3 38. Nxc3 Bxa3 39. Nxa4 Kg7 40. Ke3 Bc1+ 41. Kd4 Kf6
42. Nc5 Bf4 43. g3 Bc7 44. Kd5 Ke7 45. f4 h5 46. Nd3 Bb8 47. Ne5 Bc7 48. Nc6+
Kf6 49. e5+ Kg7 50. Nd4 Bb6 51. Nf3 Ba7 52. Kd6 Kf8 53. Kd7 Be3 54. Ng5 Bg1 55.
